approxToolTip_facebookReach.en: REACH is the number of unique people your ad was served to. We store this metric per day for each ad. When viewing this metric for more than one day (or for multiple ads in the same ad set or campaign), the related REACH values displayed may be greater than what is displayed at Facebook. When we aggregate value for multiple days (or for multiple ads in the same ad set or campaign), we are unable to adjust the values to account for unique visitors who may have been served the same ad on multiple days (or multiple ads in the same ad set or campaign).

approxToolTip_facebookFrequency.en: FREQUENCY is the average number of times your ad was served to each person (i.e. IMPRESSIONS divided by REACH). We store this metric per day, per ad. When viewing this metric for more than one day (or for multiple ads in the same ad set or campaign), the related FREQUENCY values displayed may be less than what is displayed at Facebook. When we aggregate value for multiple days (or for multiple ads in the same ad set or campaign), we are unable to adjust the values to account for unique visitors who may have been served the same ad on multiple days (or multiple ads in the same ad set or campaign).
